<% content_for :title, "Tools" %>

<h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-900 mb-2">Tools</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mb-8 max-w-2xl">
  Ongoing maintenance. Re-sync Calibre, scan the ingest folder manually, run KEPUB
  conversions. For first-time setup, see
  <%= link_to "Setup", setup_path, class: "underline hover:text-stone-700" %>.
</p>

<div class="space-y-8 max-w-2xl">
  <%# Re-sync from Calibre. %>
  <% if @calibre_db_available %>
    <section class="border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6 bg-white">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-2">Re-sync from Calibre</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 mb-4">
        Picks up any books you've added to Calibre since the last sync. The import is
        idempotent — books already in Tsundoku update in place, nothing is created twice.
      </p>
      <% if @calibre_import_in_progress %>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-700">An import is already running.</p>
      <% else %>
        <%= button_to "Re-sync from Calibre",
              library_import_path,
              method: :post,
              form: { data: { turbo_confirm: "Re-sync the Calibre library now?" } },
              class: "inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1.5 bg-white border border-stone-300 text-stone-700 text-sm font-medium rounded-md hover:bg-stone-50 transition cursor-pointer" %>
      <% end %>
    </section>
  <% end %>

  <%# Manual ingest scan. %>
  <section class="border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6 bg-white">
    <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-2">Scan ingest folder</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 mb-4">
      Drop EPUB files into the ingest directory and Tsundoku will move them into the library.
      Eventually this will run on a schedule; until then, the
      <%= link_to "Ingest page", ingest_index_path, class: "underline hover:text-stone-700" %>
      shows pending files and lets you kick off a scan.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-stone-500">
      <%= @pending_ingest_count %> <%= "file".pluralize(@pending_ingest_count) %> waiting.
    </p>
  </section>

  <%# Author-name cleanup. Walks every Author row through
      AuthorNameNormalizer; renames the dirty ones, splits joined
      multi-author rows, drops placeholders. %>
  <section class="border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6 bg-white">
    <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-2">Clean up author names</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 mb-4">
      OPF metadata from some sources joins multiple authors with <code>|</code>
      or <code>;</code>, writes names surname-first, or carries placeholders
      like "Unknown Author". This walks every Author row through the same
      normalizer the ingest pipeline uses and reshapes the dirty ones in
      place — rename, split into separate authors, merge with an existing
      match, or drop. Safe to re-run.
    </p>
    <% if @author_cleanup_in_progress %>
      <p class="text-sm text-amber-700">A cleanup is already running.</p>
    <% else %>
      <%= button_to "Clean up author names",
            cleanup_authors_tools_path,
            method: :post,
            form: { data: { turbo_confirm: "Walk every Author through the normalizer? Existing dirty rows get renamed / split / merged in place." } },
            class: "inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1.5 bg-white border border-stone-300 text-stone-700 text-sm font-medium rounded-md hover:bg-stone-50 transition cursor-pointer" %>
    <% end %>
  </section>

  <%# Hardcover-slug backfill — documented, not executed. %>
  <section class="border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6 bg-white">
    <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-2">Backfill Hardcover slugs</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 mb-4">
      Stamps Hardcover's author/series slugs onto local records so the
      "More by this author" and "More in this series" sections appear. Useful
      after a Calibre import or a CWA migration where books already have
      authors but Hardcover lookups never ran. Idempotent — re-running skips
      records that already carry a slug.
    </p>
    <pre class="bg-stone-900 text-stone-100 text-xs p-3 rounded-md overflow-x-auto"><code>docker exec -it &lt;container&gt; bin/rails enrichment:backfill_slugs</code></pre>
  </section>

  <%# KEPUB rake commands — documented, not executed. %>
  <section class="border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6 bg-white">
    <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-2">KEPUB conversion</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 mb-4">
      Tsundoku converts EPUBs to KEPUB automatically on ingest so the Kobo gets paragraph-level
      reading progress. These rake commands cover the edge cases:
    </p>
    <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-stone-700">
      <li>
        <p class="mb-1">Backfill missing KEPUBs (e.g. after enabling the feature for an existing library):</p>
        <pre class="bg-stone-900 text-stone-100 text-xs p-3 rounded-md overflow-x-auto"><code>docker exec -it &lt;container&gt; bin/rails kepub:backfill</code></pre>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="mb-1">Force re-convert every book (after a kepubify version bump):</p>
        <pre class="bg-stone-900 text-stone-100 text-xs p-3 rounded-md overflow-x-auto"><code>docker exec -it &lt;container&gt; bin/rails kepub:reconvert_all</code></pre>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</div>
